## Step 1: Naming Evaluation (FIRST PRIORITY)

Current function/variable names to evaluate:

- `containsCell` - checks if a grid contains a specific cell. Name accurately describes intent. Keep.
- `countNeighbors` - counts live neighbors of a cell. Accurate. Keep.
- `nextGeneration` - computes the next generation grid. Accurate. Keep.
- `survivors` - live cells that survive. Accurate. Keep.
- `adjacentDeadCells` - dead cells adjacent to live cells. Accurate. Keep.
- `born` - dead cells that become alive. Accurate. Keep.
- `neighborCount` - number of neighbors. Accurate. Keep.

All names clearly reveal their intent. No renaming needed.

