**`countNeighbors` function:**
```
const countNeighbors = (cell, cells) => {
  const [x, y] = cell;
  let neighborCount = 0;
  for (const [cx, cy] of cells) {
    if (cx === x && cy === y) continue;
    if (Math.abs(cx - x) <= 1 && Math.abs(cy - y) <= 1) neighborCount++;
  }
  return neighborCount;
};
```
- Constants: 3 (0, 1, 1) = 3
- Bindings: 6 (cell, cells, x, y, neighborCount, cx, cy) = 7
- Invocations: 4 (Math.abs x2, neighborCount++, and the ++ is assignment) = let me recount
  - Math.abs called 2 times = 4
  - Comparisons (===, ===, <=, <=) are not invocations in APP
- Conditionals: 2 (two if statements) = 8
